He may have been turned on to the guitar by legendary maestros Jimi Hendrix and Eric Clapton, but Warren Haynes went on to become a hugely influential musician in his own right. Hailing from North Carolina, this rock and blues guitarist, vocalist and songwriter, who takes the Needle Time hotseat, has been performing and recording, with bands including The Allman Brothers Band, for almost four decades. It is bound to be a fascinating chin wag with interviewer Neil McCormick.
